The paper deals with the worst-case time complexities of solving NAE-$k$-SAT and MAX-NAE-$k$-SAT approximation, which are problems related to computational complexity and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves randomized and deterministic algorithms, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with MAX-NAE-$k$-SAT approximation, which is related to optimization and approximation algorithms, and hence cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some geometric arguments related to the satisfiability of clauses, which could fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
